# SFT Recipes

Multi-backend SFT training: Megatron (ms-swift) and FSDP2+compile (Accelerate).
Target hardware: single-node 8×A100/H100 80GB.

## Structure
```
scripts/_common.sh          — shared env vars (both backends source this)
scripts/02_convert_data.py  — data conversion (backend-agnostic)
scripts/megatron/           — ms-swift + mcore-bridge (TP/PP, heavy deps)
scripts/fsdp/               — Accelerate + FSDP2 + torch.compile (light deps)
scripts/fsdp/train.py       — hand-written training loop, the core deliverable
scripts/benchmark/          — performance comparison tooling
sft-data/train.jsonl        — 18819 conversations with per-message loss
pyproject.toml              — uv project: [gpu] for megatron, [fsdp] for FSDP2
```

## Critical: Per-Message Loss
Data has `loss: true/false` on each assistant message. The FSDP train.py uses
incremental tokenization (`apply_chat_template` per message prefix) to build
exact token-level loss masks. This is the hardest part of the training script.

## Conventions
- Shell scripts are user-facing entry points
- All tunables: `: "${VAR:=default}"` in shell → argparse in Python
- Docker containers: `swift_sft` (Megatron), `fsdp_sft` (FSDP2)
- System Python in containers (no venv), Mac uses .venv for local data work
- `uv` for deps, `ruff` for linting (line-length=100)
- Chinese comments in shell, English in Python
- No unnecessary abstractions — simple scripts over frameworks

## Tech Stack
- PyTorch >= 2.6, Accelerate >= 1.4, transformers >= 4.57
- Flash Attention 2 for attention computation
- BF16 mixed precision everywhere
- Cosine LR schedule with warmup and min_lr
- safetensors checkpoints (HF-compatible)
